{"article_id":"D4KCrKcvdzSpzmvo","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"More than 300 of former Secretary of State Hillary Rodham Clinton ' s emails","depth":9},{"id":1,"text":"- or 5.1 percent of those","depth":10},{"id":2,"text":"processed so far -","depth":10},{"id":3,"text":"have been flagged for potential secret information ,","depth":8},{"id":4,"text":"the State Department reported to a federal court Monday","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"as the political furor continued to grow for the Democratic presidential candidate and her aides .","depth":6},{"id":6,"text":"A top senator has demanded","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"that Mrs. Clinton ' s attorney detail the steps","depth":9},{"id":8,"text":"he used","depth":9},{"id":9,"text":"to protect classified information in her emails ,","depth":9},{"id":10,"text":"which he kept on a flash drive at his office .","depth":9},{"id":11,"text":"ABC News reported this weekend","depth":7},{"id":12,"text":"that the Colorado company","depth":10},{"id":13,"text":"that helped run her server","depth":10},{"id":14,"text":"said","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"there may be a full backup server ,","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"which might have many of the messages","depth":10},{"id":17,"text":"she said","depth":11},{"id":18,"text":"she deleted .","depth":11},{"id":19,"text":"In the new court filing , the State Department said","depth":6},{"id":20,"text":"it is getting back on schedule","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"for publicly releasing the Clinton emails","depth":9},{"id":22,"text":"after falling more than 1,000 pages behind in July ,","depth":8},{"id":23,"text":"when the need","depth":9},{"id":24,"text":"to screen messages for secret information","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"overwhelmed the department .","depth":8},{"id":26,"text":"Now , the screening process is running smoothly ,","depth":7},{"id":27,"text":"with five security agencies involved in the review .","depth":7},{"id":28,"text":"They have been through 20 percent of Mrs. Clinton ' s messages ,","depth":9},{"id":29,"text":"the department said .","depth":9},{"id":30,"text":"Officials told the court","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"that they have found 305 messages","depth":11},{"id":32,"text":"- about 5.1 percent -","depth":11},{"id":33,"text":"that needed to be referred to the security agencies","depth":11},{"id":34,"text":"to determine","depth":12},{"id":35,"text":"whether they did , in fact , have secret information","depth":13},{"id":36,"text":"that needed to be redacted before public release .","depth":13},{"id":37,"text":"\" We ' re taking this very seriously , \"","depth":9},{"id":38,"text":"department spokesman John Kirby told reporters ,","depth":9},{"id":39,"text":"though he refused to call the revelations of classified emails on Mrs. Clinton ' s server \" troubling \" at this point .","depth":8},{"id":40,"text":"The department ' s next challenge will come later this week .","depth":4},{"id":41,"text":"A federal judge has scheduled a hearing for Thursday ,","depth":5},{"id":42,"text":"when officials will have to detail the steps","depth":7},{"id":43,"text":"they have taken","depth":7},{"id":44,"text":"to try to track down all of the messages , and any other electronics","depth":8},{"id":45,"text":"that might still hold messages ,","depth":8},{"id":46,"text":"from Mrs. Clinton and two top personal aides , Huma Abedin and Cheryl Mills ,","depth":8},{"id":47,"text":"who served in the department with her .","depth":8},{"id":48,"text":"SEE ALSO :","depth":4},{"id":49,"text":"Number of Hillary Clinton ' s emails","depth":7},{"id":50,"text":"flagged for classified data","depth":7},{"id":51,"text":"grows to 60","depth":6},{"id":52,"text":"as review continues","depth":5},{"id":53,"text":"Judicial Watch , a conservative public interest law firm","depth":11},{"id":54,"text":"that has sued","depth":12},{"id":55,"text":"to get a look at those communications ,","depth":12},{"id":56,"text":"said","depth":10},{"id":57,"text":"the department has refused to say","depth":11},{"id":58,"text":"how thorough its search has been","depth":11},{"id":59,"text":"despite Judge Emmet G. Sullivan ' s demands for more information .","depth":10},{"id":60,"text":"\" It appears as though the declarant made no effort whatsoever","depth":10},{"id":61,"text":"to find out what electronic devices the former head of the agency and two of her closest advisors used","depth":12},{"id":62,"text":"to conduct official government business for four years","depth":12},{"id":63,"text":"and where these electronic devices may be located","depth":12},{"id":64,"text":"or if they are still in existence , \"","depth":12},{"id":65,"text":"Judicial Watch said in a filing","depth":10},{"id":66,"text":"asking for the hearing .","depth":10},{"id":67,"text":"Judge Sullivan is one of several federal judges","depth":8},{"id":68,"text":"who ,","depth":9},{"id":69,"text":"responding to open-records requests ,","depth":10},{"id":70,"text":"have forced the State Department to be more forthcoming with Mrs. Clinton ' s communications .","depth":10},{"id":71,"text":"A Fox News poll","depth":9},{"id":72,"text":"released over the weekend","depth":9},{"id":73,"text":"found a public decidedly skeptical of Mrs. Clinton ,","depth":8},{"id":74,"text":"with 58 percent saying","depth":9},{"id":75,"text":"she \" knowingly lied \"","depth":10},{"id":76,"text":"when she claimed","depth":11},{"id":77,"text":"her emails didn ' t contain classified information","depth":11},{"id":78,"text":"and 54 percent thinking","depth":9},{"id":79,"text":"she put national security at risk .","depth":9},{"id":80,"text":"Mrs. Clinton rejected the use of a State.gov email account during her tenure","depth":8},{"id":81,"text":"and instead issued herself an account on a server","depth":9},{"id":82,"text":"that she kept at her home in New York .","depth":9},{"id":83,"text":"She has since acknowledged","depth":8},{"id":84,"text":"that was a bad idea .","depth":8},{"id":85,"text":"Prodded by the investigation into the 2012 terrorist attack in Benghazi , Libya ,","depth":10},{"id":86,"text":"she returned to the State Department in December some 30,000 messages","depth":11},{"id":87,"text":"that she deemed government business .","depth":11},{"id":88,"text":"She said","depth":10},{"id":89,"text":"she deleted 32,000 other messages","depth":11},{"id":90,"text":"that she deemed private .","depth":11},{"id":91,"text":"More than 60 of those messages have now had information classified ,","depth":9},{"id":92,"text":"and more than 300 , out of about 6,000","depth":12},{"id":93,"text":"that have been screened so far ,","depth":12},{"id":94,"text":"have been sent to intelligence agencies for review","depth":11},{"id":95,"text":"to determine","depth":11},{"id":96,"text":"whether they have information","depth":12},{"id":97,"text":"that needs to be redacted before release .","depth":12},{"id":98,"text":"Mrs. Clinton has insisted","depth":9},{"id":99,"text":"that she never sent any classified information from her account at all","depth":10},{"id":100,"text":"and that none of the messages","depth":13},{"id":101,"text":"she received","depth":13},{"id":102,"text":"had information","depth":14},{"id":103,"text":"that was marked classified at the time","depth":14},{"id":104,"text":"-","depth":13},{"id":105,"text":"though some of it has since been designated .","depth":11},{"id":106,"text":"\" I was permitted to , and used , a personal email","depth":11},{"id":107,"text":"and ,","depth":12},{"id":108,"text":"obviously in retrospect ,","depth":14},{"id":109,"text":"given all the concerns","depth":15},{"id":110,"text":"that have been raised ,","depth":15},{"id":111,"text":"it would have been probably smarter not to , \"","depth":13},{"id":112,"text":"she told Iowa Public Radio last week .","depth":10},{"id":113,"text":"\" But I never sent nor received any classified email ,","depth":10},{"id":114,"text":"nothing","depth":12},{"id":115,"text":"marked ' classified. '","depth":12},{"id":116,"text":"And I think","depth":12},{"id":117,"text":"this will all sort itself out . \"","depth":12},{"id":118,"text":"Internal watchdogs have contradicted Mrs. Clinton ' s account ,","depth":6},{"id":119,"text":"saying","depth":7},{"id":120,"text":"messages clearly contained classified information ,","depth":9},{"id":121,"text":"even if it wasn ' t marked as such ,","depth":9},{"id":122,"text":"and should have been kept more secure than on her own server .","depth":8},{"id":123,"text":"More recently , Mrs. Clinton ' s attorney , David E. Kendall , revealed","depth":7},{"id":124,"text":"that he kept the emails in electronic form on a flash drive","depth":8},{"id":125,"text":"stored at his office .","depth":8},{"id":126,"text":"Sen. Chuck Grassley , Iowa Republican and chairman of the Senate Judiciary Committee , said Monday","depth":11},{"id":127,"text":"that raised all sorts of questions about security","depth":12},{"id":128,"text":"- even after July ,","depth":13},{"id":129,"text":"when the State Department gave Mr. Kendall a safe","depth":14},{"id":130,"text":"in which to keep the flash drive .","depth":14},{"id":131,"text":"Mr. Grassley said","depth":12},{"id":132,"text":"it ' s questionable whether the safe was an acceptable level of security for information","depth":13},{"id":133,"text":"that now has been deemed top secret ,","depth":13},{"id":134,"text":"and demanded to know what level of security clearance Mr. Kendall has ,","depth":12},{"id":135,"text":"who issued it to him ,","depth":13},{"id":136,"text":"and what level of clearance","depth":15},{"id":137,"text":"his associates","depth":16},{"id":138,"text":"who also had access to the flash drive","depth":16},{"id":139,"text":"possessed .","depth":14},{"id":140,"text":"\" Many intelligence community personnel , uniformed personnel and the American people may be at risk","depth":12},{"id":141,"text":"when classified material is not properly secured , \"","depth":12},{"id":142,"text":"the senator wrote in his letter to Mr. Kendall ,","depth":12},{"id":143,"text":"dated Friday .","depth":12},{"id":144,"text":"\" Accordingly , it is very important that the Judiciary Committee fully understand the events","depth":11},{"id":145,"text":"that have transpired . \"","depth":11},{"id":146,"text":"Mr. Kendall ' s office said","depth":9},{"id":147,"text":"he is out of the country .","depth":9},{"id":148,"text":"A message","depth":9},{"id":149,"text":"left with another law firm employee","depth":10},{"id":150,"text":"to whom calls were referred","depth":10},{"id":151,"text":"was not returned Monday .","depth":8},{"id":152,"text":"Meanwhile , the State Department continues to try to make headway","depth":4},{"id":153,"text":"in producing the Clinton emails ,","depth":4},{"id":154,"text":"insisting","depth":4},{"id":155,"text":"that the process is running smoothly","depth":5},{"id":156,"text":"and they are back on track","depth":6},{"id":157,"text":"after falling behind Judge Sullivan ' s schedule","depth":7},{"id":158,"text":"for making all of the emails public .","depth":7},{"id":159,"text":"The reviewers have screened about 20 percent of the 30,000 emails","depth":5},{"id":160,"text":"that Mrs. Clinton returned to the department ,","depth":5},{"id":161,"text":"which means","depth":6},{"id":162,"text":"if the rate of potentially secret information remains steady ,","depth":6},{"id":163,"text":"more than 1,500 messages will have to be sent to intelligence community agencies ,","depth":7},{"id":164,"text":"known in government as \" IC , \"","depth":7},{"id":165,"text":"to screen out classified information .","depth":6},{"id":166,"text":"\" Out of a sample of approximately 20 [ percent ] of the Clinton emails , the IC reviewers have only recommended 305 documents","depth":6},{"id":167,"text":"- approximately 5.1 [ percent ] -","depth":6},{"id":168,"text":"for referral to their agencies for consultation , \"","depth":5},{"id":169,"text":"the Obama administration said in court papers .","depth":4}],"relations